00:09:16.220 --> 00:09:24.090
So, you're all probably familiar
with this story, this estimation

00:09:24.090 --> 00:09:29.190
of Franz Ferdinand and his
wife Sophia by Gavrilo Princip,

00:09:29.190 --> 00:09:31.890
down there in the lower corner.

00:09:31.890 --> 00:09:36.720
They were visiting Sarajevo
and he was essentially there

00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:40.790
to review the maneuvers
of some troops,

00:09:40.790 --> 00:09:44.490
and he had taken a
tour through the city.

00:09:46.350 --> 00:09:52.490
Princip and his associates were
funded and supplied with weapons

00:09:52.490 --> 00:09:54.630
by a group called the Black Hand.

00:09:54.630 --> 00:09:57.800
They had a relationship
with Serbian intelligence

00:09:57.800 --> 00:10:01.550
and possibly higher elements
in the Serbian government.

00:10:01.550 --> 00:10:05.540
It's still in dispute today
how high up that may have gone.

00:10:05.540 --> 00:10:09.340
But nonetheless, they were
given weapons and transported

00:10:09.340 --> 00:10:12.600
into Bosnia-Herzegovina,
which was occupied

00:10:12.600 --> 00:10:16.040
by the Austro-Hungarian Empire.

00:10:16.040 --> 00:10:22.220 position:56%
Princip and his associates lined
this road here along the [Inaudible]

00:10:22.220 --> 00:10:28.850
River, waiting for Ferdinand's
possession to come by.

00:10:29.940 --> 00:10:34.360
They fanned out along the road
with the idea being that, "Well,

00:10:34.360 --> 00:10:38.550
if you don't have a good
shot at him, let him go by.

00:10:38.550 --> 00:10:42.000
The next person will
take a shot at him."

00:10:42.000 --> 00:10:45.900
So what happens is the
entourage passes and one

00:10:45.900 --> 00:10:49.390
of the assassins throws
a bomb out onto the road.

00:10:49.390 --> 00:10:52.330
It doesn't land under
the Archduke's car,

00:10:52.330 --> 00:10:56.940
but one of his secretary's cars,

00:10:56.940 --> 00:11:02.540
and those folks are
injured by the blast.

00:11:02.540 --> 00:11:07.890
The Archduke goes to the town hall
and protests about the situation.

00:11:07.890 --> 00:11:12.430
He is advised to leave because
they say, "Well obviously,

00:11:12.430 --> 00:11:15.050
there was an attempt on your life.

00:11:15.050 --> 00:11:16.600
You should get out of
here as soon as possible.

00:11:16.600 --> 00:11:19.350
We can't ensure your security."

00:11:19.350 --> 00:11:23.420
Well, before leaving they want
to check on the injured parties

00:11:23.420 --> 00:11:26.200
and then depart from the city.

00:11:26.200 --> 00:11:31.790
Princip, while this is happening,
he's 19 and 20, it depends.

00:11:31.790 --> 00:11:35.130
There was a dispute about
his age as well at the time.

00:11:35.130 --> 00:11:39.210
And he is dejected because
he is a very ardent Bosnian

00:11:39.210 --> 00:11:41.430
Serb nationalist.

00:11:41.430 --> 00:11:44.510 position:56%
He wants to see the Archduke killed.

00:11:44.510 --> 00:11:49.010
The reason being is that this
guy has some liberalizing ideas

00:11:49.010 --> 00:11:50.310
about the Empire.

00:11:50.310 --> 00:11:54.750
They want to give their
constituent groups more autonomy.

00:11:54.750 --> 00:11:59.560
His group feels, "Well, if you
give Bosnian Serbs more autonomy

00:11:59.560 --> 00:12:03.390
that may steal the thunder
of the Pan-Serbian movement,

00:12:03.390 --> 00:12:07.590
and we want people
radicalized, not pacified."

00:12:07.590 --> 00:12:10.860
So he's sitting in a
café feeling dejected.

00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:15.240
And then what happens is they
come back down from the City Hall

00:12:15.240 --> 00:12:18.470
to this area here where
this arrow is.

00:12:18.470 --> 00:12:21.250
The driver makes a wrong turn.

00:12:21.250 --> 00:12:22.940
Princip can't believe his eyes.

00:12:22.940 --> 00:12:28.230
There's the Archduke sitting in a
car several feet in front of him.

00:12:28.230 --> 00:12:30.420
He immediately gets up, pulls
a pistol out of his jacket,

00:12:30.420 --> 00:12:33.070 position:56%
walks up to the side rail and fires,

00:12:33.070 --> 00:12:36.750
and hits the Archduke
and his wife Sophia.

00:12:38.130 --> 00:12:40.670
The Archduke implores
his wife, "Sophia,

00:12:40.670 --> 00:12:42.640
please live for the children."

00:12:42.640 --> 00:12:45.310 position:56%
They have several children together.

00:12:48.770 --> 00:12:51.200
Princip, he is supposed
to commit suicide.

00:12:51.200 --> 00:12:54.960
All the assassins actually
are supposed to commit suicide

00:12:54.960 --> 00:12:57.370
after they make an attempt.

00:12:57.370 --> 00:13:02.510
He has been given a cyanide pill
which he takes and it doesn't work.

00:13:04.070 --> 00:13:06.180
He attempts to put
the gun to his head,

00:13:06.180 --> 00:13:10.100
and security wrestles
it from his hand.

00:13:10.100 --> 00:13:14.990
He will wind up in Austrian
prison and died in 1916.

00:13:14.990 --> 00:13:18.210
He has tuberculosis at the time
that he commits this assassination.

00:13:18.210 --> 00:13:21.520
He will languish in a
prison cell and die.

00:13:22.580 --> 00:13:27.810 position:56%
So the question always is, how do we
go from this event to a world war?

00:13:27.810 --> 00:13:33.400
And the stars like Margaret
McMillan, for example,

00:13:33.400 --> 00:13:36.390
The Road to War, discusses
at length.

00:13:36.390 --> 00:13:38.270
And I encourage anyone
who is very curious

00:13:38.270 --> 00:13:41.300
about all the particular political
details that go into the making

00:13:41.300 --> 00:13:45.800
of the First World War to
dig into books such as that.

00:13:48.390 --> 00:13:57.620 position:56%
So at the outset of the conflict,
we have a couple of countries lining

00:13:57.620 --> 00:14:00.550
up together because they
have diplomatic agreements.

00:14:00.550 --> 00:14:07.960
The countries in pink --
France, Russia, and England,

00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:10.810
although England is a
slight technicality here

00:14:10.810 --> 00:14:15.960
which I'll mention -- is that they
agreed to a mutual defense pact.

00:14:15.960 --> 00:14:19.380
England has agreed in principle,

00:14:19.380 --> 00:14:22.200
and their militaries
have discussed plans

00:14:22.200 --> 00:14:24.290
of mutual defense should
it be necessary,

00:14:24.290 --> 00:14:29.060
but they are not a signatory
towards any defense pact.

00:14:29.060 --> 00:14:34.940
Germany, Austria-Hungary, and Italy
also have a mutual defense pact.

00:14:34.940 --> 00:14:41.600 position:56%
What the Austro-Hungarians wanted
to do is they want to invade Serbia.

00:14:42.830 --> 00:14:46.890
Well, Russia says, "If
you invade Serbia --

00:14:46.890 --> 00:14:49.110
" And they consider
Serbia, it's been said,

00:14:49.110 --> 00:14:51.700
is the little brother of Russia.

00:14:51.700 --> 00:14:53.000
It's not a pejorative term.

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:57.830
It's sort of a very familial
term in that part of the world.

00:14:57.830 --> 00:15:01.180
They said, "If you attack
here, we'll attack here."

00:15:01.180 --> 00:15:04.330
The Austro-Hungarians then
turned to the Germans for help.

00:15:04.330 --> 00:15:07.340
They said, "We can't defend the
Russians and attack Serbia at once.

00:15:07.340 --> 00:15:09.640
We don't have enough troops."

00:15:10.920 --> 00:15:14.140
So, this is where our complication
begins, with the Germans,

00:15:14.140 --> 00:15:16.660
and this is how we get a world war.

00:15:19.720 --> 00:15:22.140
And I'm going to skip forward
and explain that and come back

00:15:22.140 --> 00:15:24.120 position:56%
to all the belligerents in a second.

00:15:24.120 --> 00:15:28.270
There's something called
the von Schlieffen plan.

00:15:28.270 --> 00:15:34.960
The Germans said, "Our big
enemies are France and Russia."

00:15:34.960 --> 00:15:40.240
Now, if Russia mobilizes
against Austria-Hungary

00:15:40.240 --> 00:15:45.440
over this Serbia issue, that
means France will mobilize too.

00:15:45.440 --> 00:15:48.450 position:56%
If they mobilize their troops first,

00:15:48.450 --> 00:15:53.230
they have a distinct
advantage of us if we wait.

00:15:53.230 --> 00:15:55.360
So we must mobilize.

00:15:55.360 --> 00:16:00.040 position:56%
But the problem with mobilization in
Germany is this von Schlieffen plan.

00:16:00.040 --> 00:16:04.960
It's been kept a secret since
1905, when it was first conceived

00:16:04.960 --> 00:16:07.700 position:56%
and later revised through the years.

00:16:07.700 --> 00:16:12.670
And what it said was Germany
has to strike first to win.

00:16:12.670 --> 00:16:15.160
We're fighting two major
powers, France and Russia.

00:16:15.160 --> 00:16:19.510
What we want to do is hold the
Russians at bay with a small amount

00:16:19.510 --> 00:16:24.040
of forces as possible, put the
