02:10:52.320 --> 02:10:55.810
Suvla Bay, when they landed at
Suvla Bay there were no Ottomans

02:10:55.810 --> 02:10:57.750
to speak of in their way.

02:10:57.750 --> 02:10:59.880
They could have driven
those men back.

02:10:59.880 --> 02:11:01.460
With the maps have helped?

02:11:01.460 --> 02:11:02.980 position:56%
Well, maps are always going to help.

02:11:02.980 --> 02:11:05.750
But bear in mind as soon as
a map is made, it's obsolete,

02:11:05.750 --> 02:11:07.290
it's out of date immediately.

02:11:07.290 --> 02:11:09.040
So you can't blame a map.

02:11:09.040 --> 02:11:12.030
This is a man who is
scapegoating this map, is Hamilton.

02:11:12.030 --> 02:11:14.710
And I would say there's a chance.

02:11:14.710 --> 02:11:17.730
No modern historian would
argue there was a chance.

02:11:17.730 --> 02:11:19.780
Everybody would say it
was doomed to failure.

02:11:19.780 --> 02:11:21.710
But I don't know -- I'm
a bit of an optimist.

02:11:21.710 --> 02:11:25.250
Maybe, just maybe, if we had had
