02:17:54.590 --> 02:18:00.440
&gt;&gt; Yeah, how crucial was
that knifelike ridge?

02:18:00.440 --> 02:18:01.740
Which

02:18:01.740 --> 02:18:03.040
&gt;&gt; Richard Pflederer:
On razor's edge?

02:18:03.040 --> 02:18:06.030
&gt;&gt; Peter Doyle: The razors
edge was -- How crucial was it?

02:18:06.030 --> 02:18:09.000
Well, one of the problems we have
is, as the Anzacs are coming ashore

02:18:09.000 --> 02:18:12.760
and the argument goes that they
landed too far to the north.

02:18:12.760 --> 02:18:15.230
That means they were
facing that first ridge.

02:18:15.230 --> 02:18:18.730
And as the first ridge breaks
down into the knifelike edge,

02:18:18.730 --> 02:18:22.510 position:56%
